== English ==
=== Etymology ===
A replacement of the "[[Christ]]" in [[for Christ's sake]] for a name of a disciple to [[euphemise]] it.
=== Interjection ===
'''[[for]] [[Pete]]'s [[sake]]'''
# {{idiom}} {{euphemism}} Expresses [[frustration]], [[exasperation]], [[annoyance]]
#: '''''For Pete's sake''', get off the [[computer]]! You've been on there for ages!''
